# How can you pick a random item from a list or tuple? 

Python has an in-built module called Random which enables us to 
pick random elements from a sequence such as list or tuple.

To pick a random item from a list(or tuple) we will use the 
.choice() method of Random library. It will pick any random 
element.

e.g:-   import random as r

        lst=[12,14,2,56,4,66]

        # Storing that random element in a variable named 'ans'
        ans=r.choice(lst)

        print(ans)